🔹 Rule (Golden Rule)

👉 The table written after FROM = LEFT
👉 The table written after JOIN = RIGHT
----------------------------------------------------------------------
if we want only the paid orders

SELECT
    o.order_id,
    o.order_code,
    o.status,
    o.total_amount,
    c.name AS customer_name,
    c.city
FROM customers c
RIGHT JOIN orders o
    ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
WHERE o.status = 'PAID'
ORDER BY o.order_id;

Filtering with WHERE o.status = 'PAID' keeps only PAID orders, but still preserves unmatched orders because the filter is applied on the right table (orders).

