SELF JOIN
A SELF JOIN is when a table is joined with itself. It is commonly used to represent hierarchies such as: employee → manager

In an employee hierarchy, both the employee and the manager are stored in the same table, so we use two aliases to treat it like two different tables.

SELECT
    e.emp_name AS employee,
    m.emp_name AS manager
FROM employees e
JOIN employees m
    ON e.manager_id = m.emp_id
    ORDER BY e.emp_id;;

if any of the manager data is null then that employee will not be included as manager is missing

