NATURAL JOIN
A NATURAL JOIN automatically joins two tables by matching all columns that have the same name in both tables. Useful when both tables share a common column name and you want an automatic join without writing ON

SELECT 
  c.customer_id,
  cl.tier
FROM customers AS c
NATURAL JOIN customer_loyalty AS cl
ORDER BY c.customer_id;

Note: NATURAL JOIN can be risky in real projects because:

If later both tables gain another same-named column (e.g. name), the join will silently start matching on both columns.
This can change results without warning.